    
Instalar mysql:

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install mysql-server
sudo mysql_secure_installation

systemctl status mysql.service


Instalar python 2.7:

sudo apt-get install build-essential checkinstall
$ sudo apt-get install libreadline-gplv2-dev libncursesw5-dev libssl-dev libsqlite3-dev tk-dev libgdbm-dev libc6-dev libbz2-dev
$ cd /usr/src
sudo wget https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.13/Python-2.7.13.tgz
sudo tar xzf Python-2.7.13.tgz
$ cd Python-2.7.13
$ sudo ./configure
$ sudo make altinstall

Instalar django:

sudo apt-get install python-pip
sudo apt-get install libmysqlclient-dev
En Mac: export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/mysql/bin
pip install mysqlclient
sudo apt install python-django-common
sudo apt-get install python-django
pip install lxml

Crear un proyecto:

django-admin startproject mysite
python manage.py startapp polls

python manage.py runserver


Instalación apache2:

sudo apt-get install apache2
service apache2 restart
service apache2 stop
service apache2 start

Instalación phpmyadmin:

apt-get install phpmyadmin
en /etc/apache2/apache2.conf añadir: Include /etc/phpmyadmin/apache.conf
service apache2 restart
http://localhost/phpmyadmin/
http://127.0.0.1/phpmyadmin/


Comandos inicializacion de proyecto:

pip install lxml
pip install suds
pip install xmltodict
pip install pymysql
pip install Imaging-1.1.7.tar.gz
pip install django_messages
pip install django-contrib-comments
pip install requests
pip install django-tinymce
pip install social-auth-app-django
pip install pycrypto
Pip Install tagging

modificado storage_engine default_storage_engine



Git commands:

git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
git config --global user.name "Your Name"

Ver puertos:

sudo netstat -lp --inet 
fuser 8000/tcp
fuser -k 8080/tcp


